%% Argo Workflows - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant DSP as DSP API Server
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant WFC as workflow-controller<br/>9090/TCP metrics, 6060/TCP health
    participant Pod as Workflow Pod<br/>(argoexec sidecar)
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO Storage<br/>443/TCP or 9000/TCP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/TCP or 3306/TCP
    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Note over DSP,DB: Flow 1: Workflow Execution (DSP Pipeline Run)

    DSP->>K8sAPI: POST Workflow CR<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>WFC: Watch notification (Informer)<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    WFC->>K8sAPI: Create Pod for workflow step<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Pod: Pod scheduled & started

    Pod->>K8sAPI: Patch WorkflowTaskResult<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Pod->>S3: Upload artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Access Key/Secret Key
    S3-->>Pod: Upload confirmation

    WFC->>K8sAPI: Update Workflow status<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over WFC,DB: Flow 2: Workflow Archiving (Optional)

    WFC->>DB: Archive completed workflow<br/>TCP/5432 or 3306<br/>TLS optional<br/>Auth: Username/Password
    DB-->>WFC: Confirmation

    Note over Prom,WFC: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    Prom->>WFC: Scrape /metrics<br/>HTTP/9090<br/>plaintext<br/>Auth: None
    WFC-->>Prom: Metrics response
